# Rule 001 — File & Folder Structure

## Canonical Directory Layout

```
project-root/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/                        # All Cursor rule files
├── app/                              # Next.js App Router pages & layouts
│   ├── (auth)/                       # Route group: auth pages (login, register)
│   │   └── login/
│   │       └── page.tsx
│   ├── (dashboard)/                  # Route group: authenticated pages
│   │   └── layout.tsx
│   ├── api/                          # Next.js API route handlers
│   │   └── [resource]/
│   │       └── route.ts
│   ├── layout.tsx                    # Root layout
│   ├── page.tsx                      # Root page
│   └── globals.css                   # Global CSS (only Tailwind directives here)
│
├── components/                       # All React components
│   ├── ui/                           # Primitive/atomic components (Button, Input, Modal…)
│   ├── layout/                       # Layout components (Navbar, Sidebar, Footer…)
│   ├── features/                     # Feature-specific component groups
│   │   └── [feature-name]/           # e.g. components/features/auth/
│   └── shared/                       # Cross-feature reusable components
│
├── lib/                              # Pure logic, utilities, and integrations
│   ├── api/                          # API client functions (one file per resource)
│   ├── auth/                         # Auth helpers and config
│   ├── db/                           # Prisma client and DB utilities
│   ├── hooks/                        # Custom React hooks
│   ├── store/                        # Zustand stores (one file per domain)
│   ├── utils/                        # Pure utility functions
│   └── validations/                  # Zod schemas (one file per domain)
│
├── types/                            # TypeScript types and interfaces
│   ├── api.ts                        # API request/response types
│   ├── auth.ts                       # Auth-related types
│   └── index.ts                      # Barrel export for all types
│
├── prisma/                           # Prisma schema and migrations
│   ├── schema.prisma
│   └── migrations/
│
├── public/                           # Static assets
│   ├── images/
│   ├── icons/
│   └── fonts/
│
├── config/                           # App-level configuration constants
│   ├── constants.ts                  # App-wide constants (never env vars)
│   ├── routes.ts                     # Centralized route definitions
│   └── metadata.ts                   # SEO/metadata config
│
├── tests/                            # Test utilities and global test setup
│   └── setup.ts
│
└── [config files]                    # package.json, tsconfig, tailwind, eslint, etc.
```

## Naming Conventions

| Item | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| React components | PascalCase | `UserCard.tsx` |
| Component folders | PascalCase (co-located) | `UserCard/index.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase prefixed `use` | `useAuthUser.ts` |
| Utility functions | camelCase | `formatCurrency.ts` |
| Zustand stores | camelCase suffixed `Store` | `authStore.ts` |
| Zod schemas | camelCase suffixed `Schema` | `loginSchema.ts` |
| API route handlers | `route.ts` (Next.js convention) | `app/api/users/route.ts` |
| Types/interfaces | PascalCase | `UserProfile`, `ApiResponse<T>` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT` |
| CSS class files | kebab-case | `user-card.module.css` |
| Test files | Same name + `.test` or `.spec` | `UserCard.test.tsx` |

## Rules

1. **One component per file.** No exporting multiple components from a single file.
2. **Co-locate tests.** A component test lives next to the component, not in a separate `__tests__` folder, unless it is a global test utility.
3. **Feature folders own their dependencies.** A feature in `components/features/auth/` imports only from `lib/`, `components/ui/`, or `types/`. It never imports from another feature folder directly.
4. **No barrel files in `app/`.** Only use `index.ts` barrel exports in `components/`, `lib/`, and `types/`.
5. **API route files are thin.** Route handlers in `app/api/` call service functions in `lib/api/` — no business logic inside route handlers.
6. **All routes are defined in `config/routes.ts`.** Never hardcode route strings in components.

## Prohibited

- ❌ Files placed at the project root other than config files (package.json, tsconfig, etc.)
- ❌ Components inside `app/` — move to `components/`
- ❌ Business logic inside page or layout files
- ❌ Import paths using `../../../` more than 2 levels deep — use `@/` aliases instead
- ❌ Files named `index.tsx` for components (except inside named folders); use descriptive names
